%N A258763 Decimal expansion of Ls_7(Pi/3), the value of the 7th basic generalized log-sine integral at Pi/3 (negated).
%H A258763 Jonathan M. Borwein and Armin Straub, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/1993886.1993899">Special values of generalized log-sine integrals</a>, ISSAC '11: Proceedings of the 36th international symposium on Symbolic and algebraic computation, 2011, pp. 43-50; <a href="https://carmamaths.org/resources/jon/logsin3.pdf">alternative link</a>.
%F A258763 Equals -Integral_{0..Pi/3} log(2*sin(x/2))^6 dx. [corrected by _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 29 2026]
%F A258763 Equals -74369*Pi^7/326592 - (15/2) * Pi * Zeta[3]^2 + 135*Gl_{6, 1}(Pi/3), where Gl is the multiple Glaisher function.
%F A258763 Equals -720 * 8F7(1/2,1/2,...; 3/2,3/2,...; 1/4) (with 8F7 the hypergeometric function). [corrected by _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 29 2026]
%e A258763 -720.0413727026361868324054384156808323219739773138289507099468607266...
%t A258763 RealDigits[-720*HypergeometricPFQ[Table[1/2, {8}], Table[3/2, {7}], 1/4], 10, 103] // First (* corrected by _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 29 2026 *)
%o A258763 (PARI) -intnum(x = 0, Pi/3, log(2*sin(x/2))^6) \\ _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 29 2026
